1
00:01:31,700 --> 00:01:34,930
[NORTHWARD]

2
00:01:35,100 --> 00:01:37,050
[Episode 6]

3
00:01:48,259 --> 00:01:49,330
Why did you try to wreck the car?

4
00:01:51,130 --> 00:01:52,880
Crippled Sun didn't pay his debts.

5
00:01:53,220 --> 00:01:54,810
My mom cried all night at home.

6
00:01:54,910 --> 00:01:56,200
I just couldn't take it anymore.

7
00:01:59,110 --> 00:02:01,380
The police's talk with you that day did work.

8
00:02:01,740 --> 00:02:03,050
If this were before,

9
00:02:03,120 --> 00:02:04,710
you'd have smashed the car for sure,

10
00:02:04,740 --> 00:02:06,350
and then been caught on camera,

11
00:02:06,350 --> 00:02:07,540
making your parents pay for it.

12
00:02:10,070 --> 00:02:11,220
Honestly, I was worried about that.

13
00:02:12,800 --> 00:02:14,750
At worst, I'd take responsibility myself.

14
00:02:16,910 --> 00:02:18,120
I just feel that

15
00:02:18,670 --> 00:02:20,030
I'm about to turn eighteen,

16
00:02:20,390 --> 00:02:21,560
and I wanna change the way I live

17
00:02:22,900 --> 00:02:24,390
instead of acting recklessly.

18
00:02:24,870 --> 00:02:26,060
Siyi was right.

19
00:02:26,550 --> 00:02:28,400
I should seriously think about my future path.

20
00:02:29,030 --> 00:02:30,400
Don't worry,

21
00:02:30,400 --> 00:02:31,870
you'll be fine.

22
00:02:33,590 --> 00:02:34,990
You'll make a big fortune in the future.

23
00:02:38,390 --> 00:02:39,390
How do you know that?

24
00:02:40,030 --> 00:02:41,630
I've known it since childhood.

25
00:02:42,180 --> 00:02:43,790
I knew it from the first time

26
00:02:43,790 --> 00:02:45,390
I helped my mom watch the stall

27
00:02:45,390 --> 00:02:46,240
on the street.

28
00:02:52,640 --> 00:02:54,230
Three youtiao.

29
00:02:54,550 --> 00:02:56,220
Three bowls of soy milk.

30
00:02:56,350 --> 00:02:58,070
One yuan and fifty cents in total.

31
00:02:58,070 --> 00:02:58,680
Pay now.

32
00:02:59,850 --> 00:03:01,170
Pay for what?

33
00:03:01,910 --> 00:03:03,430
No payment, no food!

34
00:03:03,430 --> 00:03:03,990
What are you doing?

35
00:03:03,990 --> 00:03:04,950
Give me the youtiao.

36
00:03:04,950 --> 00:03:06,100
Give me that!

37
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:07,480
Give it to me!

38
00:03:07,480 --> 00:03:08,720
What's wrong, Fenghua?

39
00:03:08,830 --> 00:03:10,270
Madam, he's not paying!

40
00:03:10,270 --> 00:03:10,670
I'll pay.

41
00:03:10,670 --> 00:03:11,710
Mom, you don't need to pay.

42
00:03:12,430 --> 00:03:13,420
Why?

43
00:03:13,870 --> 00:03:15,070
I gave her mom a good idea.

44
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:17,060
And she said I could eat anything for free.

45
00:03:17,270 --> 00:03:17,910
What idea?

46
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:19,030
Why don't I know about this?

47
00:03:19,390 --> 00:03:20,660
I told your mom that,

48
00:03:19,579 --> 00:03:23,380
[Breakfast]

49
00:03:21,190 --> 00:03:22,590
with the crowds on Flower Street

50
00:03:22,790 --> 00:03:24,110
and everything being so cheap,

51
00:03:24,150 --> 00:03:26,230
despite a whole morning of her hard work,

52
00:03:26,290 --> 00:03:27,530
she would only

53
00:03:27,590 --> 00:03:29,480
earn a little bit of money.

54
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:30,540
I suggested

55
00:03:30,579 --> 00:03:32,180
she prepare the soy milk first

56
00:03:32,200 --> 00:03:34,250
and then hire someone to sell it at the school gate.

57
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:36,400
To sell various flavors of soy milk,

58
00:03:36,430 --> 00:03:38,380
like red bean, chocolate, and such.

59
00:03:38,420 --> 00:03:40,510
The daily turnover is basically

60
00:03:40,530 --> 00:03:41,560
over 100 yuan.

61
00:03:41,600 --> 00:03:42,430
Really?

62
00:03:42,440 --> 00:03:44,160
Yes! It's true, of course.

63
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:46,300
Just one casual idea from you,

64
00:03:46,470 --> 00:03:48,650
and my mom earned several hundred more each month.

65
00:03:49,020 --> 00:03:50,450
She always praised you at home.

66
00:03:50,480 --> 00:03:51,520
It drove me mad.

67
00:03:52,790 --> 00:03:54,660
That was on your dimwittedness,

68
00:03:55,190 --> 00:03:55,980
not my fault.

69
00:03:59,650 --> 00:04:02,560
Most people are dimwitted compared to you.

70
00:04:08,650 --> 00:04:09,360
Fenghua,

71
00:04:10,100 --> 00:04:11,110
I don't have money.

72
00:04:12,940 --> 00:04:14,600
I'm not asking you for money.

73
00:04:14,820 --> 00:04:15,920
Look how scared you are.

74
00:04:16,910 --> 00:04:19,019
You've never praised me like this before.

75
00:04:19,160 --> 00:04:20,560
It's indeed scary.

76
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:23,120
I didn't praise you

77
00:04:23,150 --> 00:04:24,310
just to keep you humble.

78
00:04:25,820 --> 00:04:26,980
Then why now?

79
00:04:29,670 --> 00:04:30,520
It'll be too late

80
00:04:31,760 --> 00:04:32,670
If I don't praise you

81
00:04:33,190 --> 00:04:33,980
before we graduate.

82
00:04:39,760 --> 00:04:40,950
How could it be too late?

83
00:04:44,150 --> 00:04:45,090
Well...

84
00:04:45,340 --> 00:04:47,750
Who knows where we'll each end up in the future?

85
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:50,210
Maybe we'll go our separate ways

86
00:04:50,250 --> 00:04:51,420
right after graduation.

87
00:04:59,210 --> 00:05:00,620
I'm definitely going to Beijing.

88
00:05:02,510 --> 00:05:03,910
So are

89
00:05:04,190 --> 00:05:05,400
Xingchi and Haikuo

90
00:05:06,030 --> 00:05:06,860
What about you?

91
00:05:11,210 --> 00:05:12,380
Depends on my mood.

92
00:05:13,040 --> 00:05:14,120
Do you want me to go with you?

93
00:05:16,270 --> 00:05:17,150
Nope.

94
00:05:18,350 --> 00:05:20,100
Then I'll go!

95
00:05:20,200 --> 00:05:22,080
I'll follow you wherever you go.

96
00:05:22,110 --> 00:05:23,640
You make money, and I'll make money too!

97
00:05:23,650 --> 00:05:24,330
You hit rock bottom,

98
00:05:24,370 --> 00:05:25,410
and I'll sit by and watch the show.

99
00:05:25,430 --> 00:05:26,310
Do I owe you something?

100
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:27,430
Yes, you do!

101
00:05:28,370 --> 00:05:30,700
You promised to buy me a car when we were kids.

102
00:05:30,840 --> 00:05:31,990
When did I say that?

103
00:05:31,990 --> 00:05:33,390
Do you have any proof?

104
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:35,100
Fine...

105
00:05:35,750 --> 00:05:36,750
I promise you.

106
00:05:38,670 --> 00:05:39,760
I'll buy you one.

107
00:05:40,820 --> 00:05:42,480
When I get my first paycheck,

108
00:05:43,760 --> 00:05:45,380
I'll buy you a car.

109
00:05:45,750 --> 00:05:46,510
What kind of car?

110
00:05:49,020 --> 00:05:50,100
A three-wheeler.

111
00:05:50,470 --> 00:05:52,290
Then you can drive it to make money.

112
00:05:52,950 --> 00:05:55,610
Five yuan to Flower Street, twenty to Huai'an.

113
00:05:56,360 --> 00:05:57,270
That's so little!

114
00:05:57,270 --> 00:05:57,950
Flower Street...

115
00:05:57,990 --> 00:05:59,230
Five yuan to Flower Street...

116
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:06,440
If you really strike it rich one day,

117
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,140
can you promise me one thing?

118
00:06:08,850 --> 00:06:09,750
What is it?

119
00:06:09,800 --> 00:06:11,460
Invite Jay Chou to our home

120
00:06:11,490 --> 00:06:13,020
and have him sing a song just for me,

121
00:06:13,040 --> 00:06:14,460
"Adorable Lady."

122
00:06:17,820 --> 00:06:19,660
Do you really think I'll make it one day?

123
00:06:20,000 --> 00:06:20,750
Of course!

124
00:06:22,990 --> 00:06:24,720
I've always believed

125
00:06:25,340 --> 00:06:27,500
you can definitely work miracles.

126
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:31,720
So,

127
00:06:32,830 --> 00:06:34,909
please have faith in yourself too.

128
00:06:47,580 --> 00:06:48,380
Fenghua,

129
00:06:48,659 --> 00:06:50,090
how about I lend you some money?

130
00:06:50,240 --> 00:06:51,240
Why?

131
00:06:51,790 --> 00:06:53,690
To buy new pants and ditch your worn-out ones.

132
00:06:53,710 --> 00:06:54,490
They're embarrassing.

133
00:06:56,470 --> 00:06:57,670
You know nothing

134
00:06:57,810 --> 00:06:59,090
about fashion.

135
00:06:59,120 --> 00:07:00,970
Have you heard of Paris Fashion Week?

136
00:07:00,990 --> 00:07:02,820
How could I not know about Paris?

137
00:07:03,070 --> 00:07:04,490
There's Notre Dame.

138
00:07:05,320 --> 00:07:06,780
And you're that

139
00:07:06,800 --> 00:07:08,920
Quasimodo.

140
00:07:11,110 --> 00:07:12,080
You...

141
00:07:12,280 --> 00:07:13,640
You love talking back, huh?

142
00:07:13,710 --> 00:07:14,510
You look so much like him!

143
00:07:14,510 --> 00:07:16,040
Would it kill you not to talk back?

144
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:19,480
You're the Quasimodo on Flower Street.

145
00:07:19,890 --> 00:07:22,120
Stop there!

146
00:07:23,430 --> 00:07:25,170
Don't hit me!

147
00:07:25,590 --> 00:07:26,890
You deserve this!

148
00:07:28,010 --> 00:07:29,150
Quasimodo!

149
00:07:31,810 --> 00:07:33,140
Stop there!

150
00:07:52,630 --> 00:07:53,880
Don't you feel cold at night?

151
00:07:55,570 --> 00:07:56,430
What's up?

152
00:07:58,530 --> 00:07:59,260
Nothing,

153
00:08:00,490 --> 00:08:01,410
I just passed by

154
00:08:02,060 --> 00:08:03,180
and wanted to drop in on you.

155
00:08:14,220 --> 00:08:15,980
I got into a fight with someone today.

156
00:08:18,180 --> 00:08:19,300
Did you win or lose?

157
00:08:20,510 --> 00:08:21,770
I lost.

158
00:08:22,480 --> 00:08:23,710
It was a total fiasco.

159
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,680
I was utterly crushed.

160
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:49,100
I don't think I've ever won

161
00:08:50,860 --> 00:08:52,570
in my entire life.

162
00:08:55,870 --> 00:08:56,960
Isn't it pathetic?

163
00:09:01,210 --> 00:09:03,010
I can't even respect myself.

164
00:09:20,540 --> 00:09:21,610
Hello, who is this?

165
00:09:21,760 --> 00:09:22,890
Hello, Zhimei.

166
00:09:22,920 --> 00:09:24,610
This is Granny Ma.

167
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,780
Granny Ma!

168
00:09:25,850 --> 00:09:26,710
Excuse me, sir.

169
00:09:26,750 --> 00:09:27,860
I need to take a call.

170
00:09:31,350 --> 00:09:32,360
Granny Ma,

171
00:09:32,650 --> 00:09:33,940
hello, what's the matter?

172
00:09:34,740 --> 00:09:36,160
Zhimei,

173
00:09:36,190 --> 00:09:37,710
How are you doing?

174
00:09:37,740 --> 00:09:38,940
I'm doing well

175
00:09:39,110 --> 00:09:40,390
and out here filming.

176
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:41,850
What's wrong?

177
00:09:41,970 --> 00:09:43,640
Did something happen at home?

178
00:09:43,680 --> 00:09:44,880
No...

179
00:09:45,670 --> 00:09:46,390
Nothing happened.

180
00:09:46,430 --> 00:09:48,070
I just missed you

181
00:09:48,070 --> 00:09:49,860
and wanted to hear your voice.

182
00:09:50,430 --> 00:09:51,460
Are you sure everything's okay?

183
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:52,880
Yeah, everything's fine.

184
00:09:54,070 --> 00:09:56,290
When are you coming back?

185
00:10:01,620 --> 00:10:02,770
It should be soon.

186
00:10:03,060 --> 00:10:04,660
I'll be back once I wrap things up.

187
00:10:07,030 --> 00:10:07,950
Okay,

188
00:10:08,170 --> 00:10:09,680
I see.

189
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:12,520
Well, filming must be quite tiring.

190
00:10:12,650 --> 00:10:14,560
Make sure to take care of yourself.

191
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:16,110
Thank you, Granny Ma.

192
00:10:16,960 --> 00:10:18,160
Then I'll hang up. Bye.

193
00:10:18,230 --> 00:10:19,350
Goodbye...

194
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:26,420
Here.

195
00:10:26,510 --> 00:10:27,520
Got it, Granny Ma.

196
00:10:27,540 --> 00:10:28,540
Thank you.

197
00:10:29,560 --> 00:10:30,540
Take care, Granny Ma.

198
00:10:46,400 --> 00:10:47,460
Listen, Xu Peng,

199
00:10:47,690 --> 00:10:48,650
you should either zero in on it

200
00:10:48,670 --> 00:10:49,920
or just quit!

201
00:10:50,380 --> 00:10:51,290
Do you hear me?

202
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:55,200
Chen Zhen,

203
00:10:55,460 --> 00:10:56,660
tell them all

204
00:10:56,680 --> 00:10:58,180
to go home if they don't wanna work.

205
00:11:02,150 --> 00:11:03,190
Yanlin.

206
00:11:06,520 --> 00:11:07,230
Granny Ma.

207
00:11:08,440 --> 00:11:09,760
Are you here for some water?

208
00:11:09,790 --> 00:11:11,980
Yes, I came to ask you for some water.

209
00:11:12,280 --> 00:11:12,930
Perfect timing.

210
00:11:13,380 --> 00:11:14,860
I just got a new batch of Pu'er tea.

211
00:11:14,890 --> 00:11:16,440
You're in for a real treat.

212
00:11:16,450 --> 00:11:17,250
Don't bother.

213
00:11:17,270 --> 00:11:19,140
-I can't tell the difference in taste anyway.
-It's okay!

214
00:11:19,170 --> 00:11:20,330
Come, please take a seat first.

215
00:11:20,830 --> 00:11:21,350
Okay.

216
00:11:21,380 --> 00:11:22,290
Just a moment.

217
00:11:27,230 --> 00:11:28,920
Why are you still standing there?

218
00:11:29,820 --> 00:11:30,630
Get back to work!

219
00:11:36,430 --> 00:11:38,010
Look how beautiful

220
00:11:38,150 --> 00:11:39,060
the tea color is!

221
00:11:39,990 --> 00:11:41,350
Just like amber.

222
00:11:41,810 --> 00:11:43,140
Dry-stored aged tea.

223
00:11:44,100 --> 00:11:45,320
I don't understand what you're saying.

224
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:47,790
I just find the tea kinda crystal-clear.

225
00:11:47,870 --> 00:11:48,840
You don't need to understand.

226
00:11:48,900 --> 00:11:49,980
Just enjoy it.

227
00:11:50,000 --> 00:11:51,200
Especially at your age,

228
00:11:51,230 --> 00:11:53,750
drinking this aged Pu'er is particularly good for your stomach.

229
00:11:54,060 --> 00:11:55,040
Care for my stomach

230
00:11:55,200 --> 00:11:56,270
and care for your liver.

231
00:11:57,130 --> 00:11:58,500
Are we sick fellows now?

232
00:12:02,740 --> 00:12:03,920
Yanlin,

233
00:12:05,540 --> 00:12:06,990
I'm actually here

234
00:12:07,030 --> 00:12:09,560
to talk to you about Zhimei.

235
00:12:11,210 --> 00:12:12,010
What's up with her?

236
00:12:13,150 --> 00:12:14,540
I heard

237
00:12:15,010 --> 00:12:17,930
she's having a tough time as an actress in Hengdian.

238
00:12:19,110 --> 00:12:19,920
It is tough.

239
00:12:21,710 --> 00:12:23,910
But the thing is, no one forced her to work there.

240
00:12:25,330 --> 00:12:27,250
I called her.

241
00:12:27,900 --> 00:12:29,120
She didn't say anything about it,

242
00:12:29,160 --> 00:12:30,880
only sharing the good news, not the bad.

243
00:12:30,960 --> 00:12:33,010
You know her personality.

244
00:12:33,040 --> 00:12:35,030
Proud and stubborn.

245
00:12:35,810 --> 00:12:38,450
No matter how much she suffers, she won't say a word.

246
00:12:39,950 --> 00:12:41,850
She must be going through a lot.

247
00:12:42,080 --> 00:12:44,070
You've been married for years.

248
00:12:44,110 --> 00:12:46,220
No grudges for too long,

249
00:12:46,250 --> 00:12:47,190
right?

250
00:12:47,220 --> 00:12:50,170
As a woman, she's at her most vulnerable right now.

251
00:12:50,190 --> 00:12:52,280
She needs your care.

252
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:54,510
Just say something sweet,

253
00:12:54,690 --> 00:12:57,090
and it'll keep her in a good mood all day.

254
00:12:57,110 --> 00:12:58,690
Even just a few words.

255
00:13:03,920 --> 00:13:12,010
[By the Canal]

256
00:13:06,290 --> 00:13:07,710
Damn it.

257
00:13:20,770 --> 00:13:22,530
You won because I let you.

258
00:13:23,070 --> 00:13:24,030
Haikuo,

259
00:13:24,140 --> 00:13:25,760
when will your mom come back?

260
00:13:26,630 --> 00:13:27,690
I dunno.

261
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:29,850
I hope she doesn't come back.

262
00:13:30,140 --> 00:13:31,100
Why?

263
00:13:31,350 --> 00:13:33,860
My mom will keep bickering with my dad if she's back.

264
00:13:34,190 --> 00:13:36,240
And I don't know how to mediate.

265
00:13:36,270 --> 00:13:37,180
It's just depressing.

266
00:13:37,230 --> 00:13:38,190
I think...

267
00:13:38,950 --> 00:13:40,390
This is still your dad's fault.

268
00:13:41,180 --> 00:13:42,400
Why?

269
00:13:42,530 --> 00:13:44,650
Look at Flower Street now.

270
00:13:45,180 --> 00:13:47,080
So many people have left.

271
00:13:47,920 --> 00:13:49,590
People always strive for better.

272
00:13:49,620 --> 00:13:51,030
What's wrong with that?

273
00:13:51,590 --> 00:13:52,830
I just hope

274
00:13:52,920 --> 00:13:56,170
the two of them can have a good talk

275
00:13:56,200 --> 00:13:57,430
and sort things out.

276
00:13:57,460 --> 00:13:59,590
Don't end up as enemies even if they get divorced

277
00:14:01,100 --> 00:14:02,960
If they really get divorced,

278
00:14:03,510 --> 00:14:04,570
who would you go with?

279
00:14:04,590 --> 00:14:05,200
My dad,

280
00:14:05,430 --> 00:14:06,630
of course!

281
00:14:07,840 --> 00:14:08,640
Why?

282
00:14:09,930 --> 00:14:10,980
My dad

283
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:13,460
is headstrong

284
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:15,540
and tends to overthink things.

285
00:14:16,580 --> 00:14:17,630
I need to look after him.

286
00:14:17,710 --> 00:14:19,030
Otherwise, he might be overwhelmed.

287
00:14:19,580 --> 00:14:20,840
I'll wait

288
00:14:19,850 --> 00:14:22,560
♫When the moon hangs in the sky♫

289
00:14:20,980 --> 00:14:21,990
until he

